    "body": "So you would like to see something like this?\r\n\r\n```\r\npragma solidity >=0.5.0 <0.7.0;\r\n\r\ncontract Test {\r\n    constructor() public { b = hex\"12345678901234567890123456789012\"; }\r\n    event Event(uint indexed a, bytes32 b);\r\n    event Event2(uint indexed a, bytes32 b);\r\n    function foo(uint a) public { emit Event(a, b); }\r\n    bytes32 b;\r\n}\r\n```\r\nwould result in the JSON:\r\n```\r\n[{\r\n\"type\":\"event\",\r\n\"inputs\": [{\"name\":\"a\",\"type\":\"uint256\",\"indexed\":true},{\"name\":\"b\",\"type\":\"bytes32\",\"indexed\":false}],\r\n\"name\":\"Event\",\r\n\"library\": \"false\",\r\n\"contractName\": \"Test\",\r\n\"sourceFile: \"test.sol\"\r\n}, {\r\n\"type\":\"event\",\r\n\"inputs\": [{\"name\":\"a\",\"type\":\"uint256\",\"indexed\":true},{\"name\":\"b\",\"type\":\"bytes32\",\"indexed\":false}],\r\n\"name\":\"Event2\",\r\n\"library\": \"false\",\r\n\"contractName\": \"Test\",\r\n\"sourceFile: \"test.sol\"\r\n}, {\r\n\"type\":\"function\",\r\n\"inputs\": [{\"name\":\"a\",\"type\":\"uint256\"}],\r\n\"name\":\"foo\",\r\n\"outputs\": [],\r\n\"library\": \"false\",\r\n\"contractName\": \"Test\",\r\n\"sourceFile: \"test.sol\"\r\n}]\r\n```\r\n\r\n@ekpyron mentions that the `abi` field is very solidity agnostic and maybe shouldn't contain such programming-language specific details.\r\n\r\nThe alternative would be what @chriseth suggested or to put it in the `metadata` object.",
